.\" Manual page for rift. Generated from cli-spec.ts;
.\" regenerate with: rift man  (or make gen-docs).
.TH RIFT 1 "2026-07-09" "rift 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rift \- expose a local port through the rift gateway
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rift
.RI "<protocol> <port> [subdomain] [options]"
.br
.B rift
.RI "\-\-set\-token <token> | \-\-set\-server <url> | \-\-set\-host <host> | \-\-set\-log\-level <level>"
.br
.B rift
.RI "completions <bash|zsh|fish>"
.br
.B rift
.RI "man"
.br
.B rift
.RI "\-\-version | \-v"
.br
.B rift
.RI "\-\-help | \-h"
.SH DESCRIPTION
rift is a self\-hosted, ngrok\-style tunnel agent. It opens a WebSocket to the rift gateway and forwards public traffic to a local port, streaming both directions.
.PP
The tunnel URL banner is printed to standard output; all diagnostics go to standard error, so a pipeline such as `rift http 3000 | ...` yields just the URL line.
.PP
The completions and man subcommands, and the \-\-set\-* flags, need neither a token nor a server: they print or persist and exit without opening a tunnel.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I protocol
Application protocol to tunnel (one of http, tcp, tls).
.RS
.TP
.B http
Forward HTTP requests; the gateway routes by subdomain and terminates TLS.
.TP
.B tcp
Forward a raw TCP stream to the local port.
.TP
.B tls
Forward a TLS stream, routed by SNI, to the local port.
.RE
.TP
.I port
Local TCP port to forward to (1..65535).
.TP
.I subdomain
Desired subdomain; the gateway picks one at random if omitted.
.SH OPTIONS
Value options accept both
.BI \-\-flag " value"
and
.BI \-\-flag= value
forms.
.TP
.BI \-\-token " token"
Gateway auth token. Overrides \fBRIFT_TOKEN\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-server " url"
Gateway ws/wss URL. Overrides \fBRIFT_SERVER\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-host " host"
Local host to forward to. Overrides \fBRIFT_HOST\fR. Defaults to \fB127.0.0.1\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-log\-level " level"
Log verbosity (debug, info, warn, error, silent). Overrides \fBRIFT_LOG_LEVEL\fR. Defaults to \fBinfo\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-insecure
Skip TLS certificate verification (wss only).
.TP
.BR \-\-version ", " \-v
Print version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-help ", " \-h
Print this help and exit.
.SH CONFIG
The
.B \-\-set\-*
flags write a value to
.B ~/.config/rift/config.json
and exit without opening a tunnel.
.TP
.BI \-\-set\-token " token"
Persist token to the config file and exit.
.TP
.BI \-\-set\-server " url"
Persist server to the config file and exit.
.TP
.BI \-\-set\-host " host"
Persist host to the config file and exit.
.TP
.BI \-\-set\-log\-level " level"
Persist log level to the config file and exit.
.PP
Precedence, highest first: command\-line flags, then environment variables, then the config file, then built\-in defaults. token and server have no default; a missing one is a hard error.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B RIFT_TOKEN
Gateway auth token (see \-\-token).
.TP
.B RIFT_SERVER
Gateway ws/wss URL (see \-\-server).
.TP
.B RIFT_HOST
Local host to forward to (see \-\-host).
.TP
.B RIFT_LOG_LEVEL
Log verbosity (see \-\-log\-level).
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for the config file; falls back to $HOME/.config.
.TP
.B HOME
Used to derive the config directory when XDG_CONFIG_HOME is unset.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/rift/config.json
.PD 0
.TP
.B ~/.config/rift/config.json
.PD
JSON config file providing token, server, host, and logLevel. Unknown keys are ignored; an invalid type or logLevel is a hard error.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Open a tunnel with a random subdomain.
.B rift http 3000
.TP
Request the subdomain "myapp".
.B rift http 3000 myapp
.TP
Forward a raw TCP port (e.g. Postgres).
.B rift tcp 5432
.TP
Save a default gateway to the config file.
.B rift \-\-set\-server wss://gw.example.com
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Clean shutdown.
.TP
.B 1
Runtime or configuration error (for example, a missing or rejected token).
.TP
.B 2
Usage error (invalid arguments).
.TP
.B 130
Terminated by SIGINT (128 + 2).
.TP
.B 143
Terminated by SIGTERM (128 + 15).
.SH SEE ALSO
Project documentation and the wire\-protocol contract ship with the source tree (README.md, docs/PROTOCOL.md).
